<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN264-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai<gap quantity="5" reason="lost" unit="character"/>uṟaiyūr iḷampoṉ vāṇikaṉār (<gap quantity="5" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ṉcāttaṉ koṟṟaṉār) pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN264">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>paraluṭai maruṅkiṟ patukkai cērtti</l>
<l>maralvakuntu toṭutta cempūṅ kaṇṇiyō</l>
<l>ṭaṇimayiṟ pīli cūṭṭip peyarpoṟit</l>
<l>tiṉinaṭ ṭaṉarē kalluṅ kaṉṟoṭu</l>
<l>kaṟavai tantu pakaiva rōṭṭiya</l>
<l>neṭuntakai kaḻintamai yaṟiyā</l>
<l>tiṉṟum varuṅkol pāṇaratu kaṭumpē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Having put together a stone heap on the side strewn with pebbles, (1)</l>
<l>putting on [it] ornate peacock feathers along with a chaplet</l>
<l>of red flowers tied after splicing bowstring hemp, engraving [his] name, (2f.)</l>
<l>they now erected a stone too. (4a-c)</l>
<l>Will the kinfolk of the bards come from today on, (7)</l>
<l>not knowing of the paragon’s having passed away (6)</l>
<l>who drove off the enemies, bringing [back] the milchcows along with the calves? (4d-5)  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
